$ Linux: root user
@ root

`root` is *the* superuser.

The superuser's → Linux/home-directory often is `→ Linux/fhs/root`.

sa:

  → Linux/user[Users in Linux]

  The → Linux/man-page#man-sections[man page section] 8 describes system management commands which can only be executed by root (such as `→ Linux/shell/commands/mount`).
